  "original_title": "22 \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc1\u0ddd\u0db0\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dda\u0dc2\u0dca\u0da8\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dab \u0db8\u0dad\u0dba \u0db8\u0dda \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba \u0d85\u0d9c\u0daf\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Supreme Court Opinion on Amendment 22 later this week",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Justice Dr. Wijayadasa Rajapaksa said in Parliament today (1) that it is hoped that the Supreme Court's opinion on the twenty-second constitutional amendment will be received by the end of this week.",
        "He also expressed confidence that after receiving the opinion of the Supreme Court, the bill can be passed in a manner that suits the country.",
        "He thus expressed his confidence by joining the debate on the second reading of the Budget Appropriation Bill.",
        "The minister said that today corruption is happening not only in the public sector but also in the private sector and also stated that about fifteen bills have been submitted to the Parliament in the past for various purposes including prevention of corruption and fraud.",
        "He said that after the adoption of the Anti-Corruption Act, the Bribery Act as well as the Assets Liabilities Law will be changed.",
        "Mr. Wijedasa Rajapaksa also said that \"our country made a mistake in money management\".",
        "The minister said that the executive took individual decisions and the sale of Hambantota port also contributed to the creation of an economic crisis in the country."
      ],
